HEADWORD: Sego
<hw>Se"go</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
liliaceous plant (<spn>Calochortus Nuttallii</spn>) of Western North
America, and its edible bulb; -- so called by the Ute Indians and the
Mormons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

